               <p>I know Mr. Miers, he is a Quaker; last Friday was se'nnight I was in Tower-street; I saw the prisoner take a handkerchief out of Mr. Miers' pocket; I secured him, then he threw down the handkerchief and I took it up.</p>
               <p>[The handkerchief was produced in court, and deposed to, and 
               <persName id="t17760417-71-person654">
                  John
                   Wade
               <interp inst="t17760417-71-person654" type="surname" value="Wade"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17760417-71-person654" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17760417-71-person654" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , servant to Mr. Miers, deposed that it was Mr. Miers' property.</p>
               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>I know no more of it than the child unborn.</p>
